insert into articles (title, image_url, content, created_at, author_id, category_id)
values ('5 Benefits of Daily Fitness', null,
        'Daily fitness routines provide proven benefits for both your body and mind. Firstly, regular exercise boosts your energy by improving cardiovascular health and increasing oxygen supply to your tissues. Secondly, it supports weight management and fat loss, making it easier to reach and maintain a healthy weight. Third, consistent physical activity has been shown to reduce the risks of chronic diseases such as diabetes, heart disease, and certain cancers. Fourth, it enhances your mood by releasing endorphins, combating anxiety and depression. Finally, engaging in daily fitness helps you sleep better, recover faster, and feel more confident in your body. Make fitness a daily habit and enjoy these lasting benefits.',
        '2025-06-16 09:10:00', 1, 1),

       ('Yoga for Beginners: Getting Started', null,
        'Yoga is a holistic practice that brings together the body, mind, and spirit. For beginners, it is important to focus on the basics: learning to breathe deeply, mastering foundational poses, and practicing mindfulness. Start with simple postures such as Mountain Pose, Downward Dog, and Child’s Pose. Always listen to your body and progress at your own pace, avoiding any movements that cause pain or discomfort. Setting a regular schedule, even if only 10 minutes a day, can help you build consistency and confidence. Over time, yoga can improve your flexibility, strength, and mental clarity. Remember, yoga is a journey, not a destination—enjoy each step along the way.',
        '2025-06-17 07:30:00', 1, 2),

       ('Cardio Workouts to Burn Fat Fast', null,
        'Cardio exercises are essential for burning calories and shedding unwanted fat. High-Intensity Interval Training (HIIT), running, cycling, and swimming are some of the most effective workouts for boosting your metabolism and accelerating fat loss. HIIT involves short bursts of intense activity followed by brief recovery periods, making your body work harder and burn more calories in less time. Consistency is key—aim for at least 150 minutes of moderate-intensity cardio each week. Always warm up before starting and cool down afterward to prevent injuries. Track your progress and mix up your routines to stay motivated and avoid plateaus.',
        '2025-06-18 18:20:00', 2, 3),

       ('Strength Training Essentials', null,
        'Strength training is crucial for building muscle, strengthening bones, and improving overall fitness. Beginners should start with compound movements such as squats, deadlifts, bench presses, and rows, which target multiple muscle groups at once. Focus on proper form and gradually increase the weight to avoid injury and ensure steady progress. It’s important to allow for rest and recovery, as muscles need time to repair and grow. Combine strength training with proper nutrition, including adequate protein intake, to maximize your results. Remember, strength is built over time—stay patient and consistent.',
        '2025-06-19 13:45:00', 2, 4),

       ('How to Build a Balanced Nutrition Plan', null,
        'Nutrition is the foundation of a healthy lifestyle. Building a balanced nutrition plan involves understanding macronutrients—proteins, carbohydrates, and fats—and how they support your body. Start by incorporating a variety of whole foods, including lean proteins, whole grains, healthy fats, fruits, and vegetables. Plan your meals ahead of time to avoid unhealthy choices and ensure you get the nutrients you need. Hydration is equally important; aim to drink at least 2 liters of water per day. Limit processed foods, added sugars, and excessive salt. Remember, balance and moderation are key—no food is off-limits, but focus on nourishing your body with quality ingredients.',
        '2025-06-20 10:00:00', 3, 5),

       ('Stretching: When and Why You Need It', null,
        'Stretching is an often-overlooked component of a well-rounded fitness routine. It improves flexibility, increases range of motion, and reduces the risk of injury. Stretching before a workout prepares your muscles for activity, while post-workout stretching aids in recovery and prevents stiffness. Incorporate both dynamic stretches (moving parts of your body through a full range of motion) before exercise, and static stretches (holding a stretch for 15-60 seconds) after. Pay special attention to tight areas such as hamstrings, calves, shoulders, and back. Make stretching a habit to keep your body limber and pain-free.',
        '2025-06-21 11:15:00', 3, 6),

       ('Staying Motivated on Your Fitness Journey', null,
        'Motivation is the driving force behind every successful fitness journey. To stay motivated, set realistic goals and break them down into manageable steps. Track your progress and celebrate small victories along the way. Find an exercise routine you enjoy, whether it’s group classes, running, or dancing, to make workouts feel less like a chore. Surround yourself with a supportive community, either in person or online. Remember that setbacks are normal; focus on building consistency rather than perfection. Visualize your success and remind yourself why you started. Persistence and patience will help you achieve your long-term goals.',
        '2025-06-22 14:00:00', 1, 7),

       ('CrossFit Explained: What to Expect', null,
        'CrossFit is a high-intensity fitness program that combines elements of weightlifting, cardio, and functional movements. Each workout, or WOD (Workout of the Day), is different, keeping your routine varied and challenging. Expect a supportive community atmosphere and friendly competition that pushes you to new limits. Beginners should start with scaled-down movements and focus on mastering technique before increasing intensity. CrossFit is suitable for all fitness levels, as workouts can be modified to match your abilities. The combination of strength, endurance, and skill development makes CrossFit a comprehensive approach to fitness.',
        '2025-06-23 16:10:00', 2, 8),

       ('Swimming for Total Body Fitness', null,
        'Swimming is a low-impact, full-body workout that builds endurance, muscle strength, and cardiovascular fitness. It’s suitable for all ages and fitness levels, making it a lifelong exercise option. Swimming engages almost every muscle group, from your core to your limbs, while being gentle on the joints. It also improves flexibility and burns calories efficiently. To get started, focus on learning proper technique for strokes such as freestyle, backstroke, and breaststroke. Incorporate interval training to build stamina. Swimming can be both relaxing and challenging, making it an excellent addition to any fitness routine.',
        '2025-06-24 08:20:00', 3, 9),

       ('Dancing for Health and Happiness', null,
        'Dancing is not only a fun and social activity but also an effective way to improve your fitness, coordination, and mood. Styles such as Zumba, hip-hop, ballet, and salsa offer different physical and mental challenges. Dancing increases your heart rate, strengthens muscles, and burns calories, while also reducing stress and boosting confidence. No special equipment is needed—just music and a willingness to move! Join a class or dance at home, invite friends, and let loose. Dancing regularly helps you stay active and brings joy to your daily life.',
        '2025-06-25 17:50:00', 1, 10);